    <note>Shi(5) Zhengzhi [1478] In 1163, his new appointment was dismissed (ba xinren) as Jiangnan Xi yunpan (SHY:ZG, 71.2b-3a has mingzi as Zhengchen in error). He was reappointed to this post in 1165. In his old age, he retired to Suzhou. In 1170, he was appointed Fayun shi when the office was re-established with headquarters at Jiangzhou. It was abolished again shortly before the end of the year. He was not a member of Shi(5) Hao's [8113] lineage (zu). Weiyang Z (1542), 19.11b. Fujian TZ, 4.7a; XNYL, 199.3a; XZZTJ, 138.7a; Shengzheng, 48.3a; SHY:ZG, 42.55b, 56a, 56b, 57a, 43.161a, 161b-162a, 162a-162b, 162b; SHY:SH, 50.20b; Suzhou FZ, 139.21b. CBD, 1, 481-2.From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:1165:  In office as Jiangnan Xi yunpan1170:  Apt. Fayun shi (office reestablished with headquarters at Jiangzhou)1170:  In office as Fayun shi1170:  In office as Fayun shi1170:  In office as Fayun shi1170:  In office as Fayun shi1170:  In office as Fayun shi1170:  (run) in office as Fayun shi1170:  In office as Fayun shi1170:  In office as Fayun shi1170:  In office as Fayun shi1170:  Out of office as Fayun shi</note>
